NEWS GOV-MO: Seven distinguished individuals were awarded honorary doctorate degrees by the University of Macau.
Today (11th) Macau University held the "2021 Honorary Degree and Higher Degree Award Ceremony" to award Macau University Honorary Doctorate Degrees to Liu Zunyi, Chen Kaixian, Nakamura Shuji, Li Lanjuan, Li Xiaoliang, Zhu Lilan and Jiang Chaohui in recognition of their outstanding achievements and significant contributions to society and education.
At the conferment ceremony, Undersecretary for Home Affairs and Education, Secretary for Social and Cultural Affairs, Mr. Au-Yeung Yu, conferred Honorary Doctoral Degrees in the presence of Chairman of the Governing Council of HKBU, Mr. Lam Kam Shing and HKBU President, Professor Song Yonghua.
Professor Liu Zunyi was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Education, Professor Chen Kaixian was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, Professor Nakamura Shuji was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, Professor Li Lanjuan was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, Professor Li Xiaoliang was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Business Administration, Professor Zhu Lilan was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, and Ms. Jiang Chaohui was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science.
In his speech, Ouyang Yu first extended his warmest congratulations and highest respect to the seven outstanding people who were awarded honorary doctorates. They have achieved remarkable accomplishments in different fields and made outstanding contributions to the country's development and the world's progress. At the same time, Ouyang Yu expressed his most sincere blessings to the graduating students and parents, and also expressed sincere respect to the university's dedicated faculty and staff who are academically exquisite.
When Professor Sun Yifeng of the College of Humanities and Medicine of the University of Macau delivered the eulogy of Professor Liu Zunyi, he said that Professor Liu Zunyi is a famous economist around the world, and is renowned for his tremendous academic accomplishments and forward-looking educational philosophy.
In addition to his achievements in economic development, growth, and East Asia economic affairs, he is also a visionary educational leader.
In short, he has made outstanding contributions to many fields.
Sun Yifeng read out a panegyric to Professor Nakamura Shūji, expressing that Professor Nakamura Shūji was a pioneer in sustainable energy technology.
He was one of the three Nobel Prize in Physics laureates in 2014 for his invention of the blue light-emitting diode (LED).
Professor Nakamura's invention not only completely changed the lighting industry, but also pushed for the production of white light emitting diodes that are now widely used in daily life and industrial production, making a great contribution to the wellbeing of mankind.
Sun Yifeng declared that Professor Li Lanjuan, as the pioneer of China's artificial liver industry, created a unique and effective Li artificial liver system, which achieved a major breakthrough in treating severe hepatitis and liver failure, significantly reducing the mortality of liver failure.
In this fight against the coronavirus, her team's proposed "4-2 Balance" program and the three technologies of artificial liver, microecology, and stem cells have significantly improved the survival rate of critical cases.
Sun Yifeng read out Li Xiaoliang's praise and said that Professor Li Xiaoliang had laid the foundation for innovation in operations management, shaped the thinking methods of supply chain theories and practices, and completely changed business models around the world.
Li Xiaoliang is renowned for popularizing the concept of the long whip effect in operations management, and exploring measures to tackle this phenomenon.
Nowadays, under the epidemic and intense economic situation, the long whip effect is increasingly highlighted, causing severe disruption of the supply chain.
Li Xiaoliang has insightful research like sending charcoal in the snow, helping the industry to cope with the difficulties, thus bringing great social value.
Sun Yifeng declared Julia's praises and said that in her research work she has found a breakthrough and innovative staining technology for sample preparation that is highly regarded among scientific peers both domestically and abroad.
She was honored with important titles such as Fellow of the International Eurasian Academy of Science with her extraordinary scientific achievements, and earned an esteemed position in the temple of world science with her brilliant performance.
When the Dean of Macao University of Chinese Medicine (AUEMC) Chen Xin read Professor Chen Kai-xian's laudatory citation, he said that Professor Chen Kai-xian had been engaged in drug development for more than 40 years, and his outstanding scientific achievements and important contributions to the nation, Macao, AUEMC, and the National Key Laboratory had earned him a lofty international position and prestige.
He fully embodies his sense of mission to dedicate to the national medical development strategy by his active promotion of the development of traditional Chinese medicine industry in Macau and the Greater Bay Area.
When the Dean of the Australian Institute of Technology had to make the speech praising Mrs. Jiang Chao Hui, he expressed that the major inventions and patents developed by Mrs. Jiang Chao Hui have accumulated more than 15 items related to storage virtualization, navigation, file system and power management, all of which are high in practicality and widely used, further enhancing the convenience of human life.
As an accomplished inventor, Ms. Jiang often simplifies complicated science and theory into easily understood concepts accessible to the general public.
Lastly, Chen Kai delivered the acceptance speech on behalf of the honorary doctorate.
He is glad to see a good example set by the medical and pharmaceutical industry in Macao and the Greater Bay Area: from the first Chinese traditional medicine quality research state key laboratory established by UM to the thriving development of Chinese medicine and pharmacy in the Greater Bay Area, UM has played an invaluable role in pooling the outstanding talents in the Chinese medicine field in the Greater Bay Area.
In addition, he believes that the management team of the University of Macao has foresight and is not only providing students with a research ground academically, but also delivering to society many responsible talents.
He is honored to be able to communicate and cooperate with AUS, and sincerely congratulates AUS on its recent achievements.
